# Details about string

## Definition

When creating an array of characters, namely string, remember to reserve a space for `'\0'`.
 
 e.g.
```
const int LEN = 80;
char sentence[LEN + 1];
```

## In `cin.getline`

When using `cin.getline`, the second parameter means the whole length or space of the string.

e.g.
```
const int LEN = 80;
char sentence[LEN + 1];
cin.getline(sentence, LEN + 1);
```
